1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:05,338
[Azuelo] Agent Marcus Reyes
hid Datu Rahman

2
00:00:05,422 --> 00:00:07,340
under my strict supervision.

3
00:00:07,424 --> 00:00:11,136
[in English] He was acting
on a clandestine operation

4
00:00:11,219 --> 00:00:13,012
officially sanctioned by the SID.

5
00:00:13,096 --> 00:00:14,639
So legally speaking, sir,

6
00:00:14,723 --> 00:00:19,102
we can't dismiss Agent Reyes from service.

7
00:00:19,185 --> 00:00:21,187
[Espina] <i>We're arresting you for violating</i>

8
00:00:21,271 --> 00:00:23,648
the Comprehensive Firearms
and Ammunition Regulation Act.

9
00:00:23,732 --> 00:00:25,191
[Solares] <i>Our agents have been discovered.</i>

10
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:29,279
[Manuel, in English] Good.
Now we can fully control the narrative.

11
00:00:29,362 --> 00:00:31,948
[in English] Congratulations,
Major Espina, Agent Angeles.

12
00:00:32,032 --> 00:00:33,992
[in English] And congratulations,
Task Force Alpha.

13
00:00:34,075 --> 00:00:35,577
[in English] Mission accomplished.

14
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:38,163
[Espina] Agent Reyes, welcome back.

15
00:00:38,246 --> 00:00:39,664
Well, looks like

16
00:00:39,748 --> 00:00:42,709
I'll be taking Task Force Alpha
back from you right away.

17
00:00:42,792 --> 00:00:46,004
Task Force Alpha
isn't complete without you.

18
00:00:46,087 --> 00:00:48,423
Marcus no longer has a case against him.

19
00:00:48,506 --> 00:00:50,216
His suspension has been lifted as well.

20
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:52,844
[goon] <i>Sir, I have the name of the woman</i>
<i>you want me to spy on.</i>

21
00:00:52,927 --> 00:00:54,262
<i>Jamilah Abubakar.</i>

22
00:00:54,345 --> 00:00:55,805
[Teresa] <i>I'm heading</i>
<i>to the ER first, okay?</i>

23
00:00:55,889 --> 00:00:58,850
I want to finish work early,
so I can prepare food at home.

24
00:00:58,933 --> 00:01:01,019
You're all coming, right?
We're celebrating.

25
00:01:01,102 --> 00:01:04,606
[Teresa] <i>I already told Marcus</i>
<i>to invite his entire team.</i>

26
00:01:04,689 --> 00:01:06,941
Felix and Lara can't make it.

27
00:01:07,025 --> 00:01:10,612
The only ones missing
are Jamilah and Gracia.

28
00:01:10,695 --> 00:01:12,530
- Jamilah's coming?
- And Gracia too?

29
00:01:12,614 --> 00:01:14,616
- Why don't you go pick them up, son?
- Okay.

30
00:01:14,699 --> 00:01:18,536
I'll finally get my revenge
on you, Jalil Abubakar.

31
00:01:18,620 --> 00:01:23,500
[Felix] <i>This time, I'll use your sister</i>
<i>to lure you out of hiding.</i>

32
00:01:23,583 --> 00:01:24,834
<i>Coward!</i>

33
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:29,714
[mysterious theme music playing]

34
00:01:42,143 --> 00:01:45,021
- [suspenseful music playing]
- [Jamilah shrieks]

35
00:01:45,939 --> 00:01:47,273
[man shouts]

36
00:01:47,357 --> 00:01:49,234
[Jamilah] Peter! Gracia!

37
00:01:49,317 --> 00:01:51,569
- [Gracia] Help!
- [horn honks, tires screeching]

38
00:01:52,821 --> 00:01:55,657
- [suspenseful music continues]
- [car door slams shut]

39
00:01:58,034 --> 00:01:59,953
- Sir Marcus!
- [Peter] Jamilah!

40
00:02:00,036 --> 00:02:01,037
[Marcus] Hey!

41
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:07,377
- [blow lands]
- [man grunting]

42
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:09,003
[man screaming]

43
00:02:09,087 --> 00:02:10,380
‪[grunting and groaning]

44
00:02:11,506 --> 00:02:14,175
[man screaming]

45
00:02:14,259 --> 00:02:16,094
[Peter panicking]

46
00:02:16,177 --> 00:02:18,179
‪[grunting and groaning]

47
00:02:18,263 --> 00:02:19,889
[grunting and groaning]

48
00:02:19,973 --> 00:02:21,182
- [man grunting]
- [blow lands]

49
00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:30,525
[Gracia whimpering]

50
00:02:33,486 --> 00:02:36,489
[music intensifies]

51
00:02:41,953 --> 00:02:45,582
[Peter breathing heavily]

52
00:02:45,665 --> 00:02:47,208
[Peter] Jamilah…

53
00:02:47,292 --> 00:02:48,501
Oh, God. Oh, God.

54
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:51,462
[frustrated grunt]

55
00:02:52,547 --> 00:02:54,424
[tires screeching]

56
00:02:56,259 --> 00:02:57,969
Your day will come.

57
00:02:58,928 --> 00:03:00,346
[scoffs]

58
00:03:03,141 --> 00:03:08,271
[pensive music playing]

59
00:03:08,354 --> 00:03:09,439
You're pretty good.

60
00:03:12,942 --> 00:03:13,818
Are you okay?

61
00:03:13,902 --> 00:03:15,403
- We're okay, Sir Marcus.
- We're fine.

62
00:03:15,486 --> 00:03:17,030
- [Peter] We're okay.
- Get in the car.

63
00:03:17,113 --> 00:03:18,239
- Let's go.
- Okay.

64
00:03:18,323 --> 00:03:19,866
[Gracia] Hurry.

65
00:03:19,949 --> 00:03:21,618
It's good that I called you earlier.

66
00:03:22,410 --> 00:03:26,247
[unsettling music playing]

67
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:29,959
[tires screeching]

68
00:03:31,169 --> 00:03:33,838
Damn you, Marcus.

69
00:03:34,672 --> 00:03:36,174
You ruined my plan.

70
00:03:36,966 --> 00:03:39,135
Auntie, if only you'd seen them before.

71
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:42,347
Sir Marcus and Major Espina
used to clash all the time.

72
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:45,099
Usman had to step in
and break them up, Auntie.

73
00:03:45,183 --> 00:03:45,975
Oh?

74
00:03:46,059 --> 00:03:48,269
Auntie, they were this close
to throwing punches

75
00:03:48,353 --> 00:03:49,771
right in the middle of an operation.

76
00:03:49,854 --> 00:03:51,064
- Really?
- [Liam chuckles] Oh!

77
00:03:51,147 --> 00:03:55,985
Auntie, remember that hostage situation
at your hospital?

78
00:03:56,069 --> 00:03:58,238
Major, sorry. I'll tell the story anyway.

79
00:03:58,321 --> 00:03:59,447
It's all over now.

80
00:03:59,530 --> 00:04:02,784
Even when we arrived,
they were still arguing.

81
00:04:02,867 --> 00:04:04,494
We were already outside the hospital!

82
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:05,870
[laughter]

83
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:09,249
Well, they both have strong personalities.

84
00:04:09,332 --> 00:04:12,418
That's why they didn't get along at first.

85
00:04:12,502 --> 00:04:15,797
But what matters is that you saved us.

86
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:19,425
And more importantly,
they get along now, right?

87
00:04:20,051 --> 00:04:23,054
[unsettling music playing]

88
00:04:25,056 --> 00:04:26,307
[car door chimes]

89
00:04:40,488 --> 00:04:43,616
[unsettling music continues]

90
00:04:45,910 --> 00:04:47,370
Sir Marcus.

91
00:04:47,453 --> 00:04:48,288
Are you okay?

92
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:52,625
I'm just making sure
no one's following us, Jamilah.

93
00:04:54,002 --> 00:04:56,713
How about you? Are you okay?

94
00:04:56,796 --> 00:04:58,172
I'm fine.

95
00:04:58,256 --> 00:04:59,799
Are you okay, Gracia? Peter?

96
00:04:59,882 --> 00:05:01,009
We're okay.

97
00:05:01,551 --> 00:05:03,052
You're pretty brave, girl.

98
00:05:03,136 --> 00:05:05,221
- Yeah.
- Of course.

99
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:06,556
I'm Tausug.

100
00:05:09,475 --> 00:05:12,103
- So you know how to…
- Mm-hmm.

101
00:05:13,021 --> 00:05:15,523
My brother taught me how to fight.

102
00:05:15,606 --> 00:05:17,567
[in Bisaya] Wait.

103
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:21,487
Who were those people
who tried to abduct you?

104
00:05:21,571 --> 00:05:22,864
Jamilah.

105
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:27,076
Do you know anyone who'd do
something like this to you?

106
00:05:29,412 --> 00:05:30,955
Yes.

107
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:32,957
A lot of people.

108
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:35,835
Because I'm Datu Rahman's daughter.

109
00:05:35,918 --> 00:05:38,921
[tense music playing]

110
00:05:41,799 --> 00:05:45,219
Now they're practically inseparable.
They're always together.

111
00:05:45,887 --> 00:05:48,973
Whenever we see them,
they look more like brothers.

112
00:05:49,057 --> 00:05:51,142
[chuckles] That could work. Right, Auntie?

113
00:05:51,225 --> 00:05:52,435
You guys are unbelievable.

114
00:05:52,518 --> 00:05:55,271
Just because Reyes isn't here,
you're taking advantage of it.

115
00:05:55,354 --> 00:05:56,939
- Hey, come on!
- [Teresa] Seriously!

116
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:59,150
- He's defending Sir Marcus!
- Stop that.

117
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:01,110
- Mom, we're here.
- [Teresa] Oh, son.

118
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:02,528
Why did it take you so long?

119
00:06:02,612 --> 00:06:04,822
Someone tried to kidnap Jamilah.

120
00:06:04,906 --> 00:06:06,282
- What?
- Huh?

121
00:06:06,949 --> 00:06:08,743
- [Marcus] It's true.
- Jamilah, are you okay?

122
00:06:08,826 --> 00:06:10,244
Jamilah, what happened?

123
00:06:10,328 --> 00:06:13,748
[tense music playing]

124
00:06:13,831 --> 00:06:14,957
You know each other?

125
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:17,877
[tense music continues]

126
00:06:19,003 --> 00:06:22,590
Uh, yes. I met her
when I picked up Datu Rahman.

127
00:06:23,382 --> 00:06:25,551
That's probably why her life
is in danger too.

128
00:06:25,635 --> 00:06:28,429
[tense music continues]

129
00:06:30,515 --> 00:06:31,516
[Eve] Wait.

130
00:06:31,599 --> 00:06:33,518
Datu Rahman is your father?

131
00:06:35,978 --> 00:06:38,189
That's why we need to protect her.

132
00:06:39,607 --> 00:06:43,027
Did you see who tried to abduct you?

133
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:45,196
No.

134
00:06:45,863 --> 00:06:47,365
We… we didn't.

135
00:06:47,448 --> 00:06:50,993
They were wearing masks. And I think

136
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:53,287
they'd been watching Jamilah
for a long time.

137
00:06:53,371 --> 00:06:56,833
While we were waiting
for a ride outside the hospital,

138
00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:58,084
they attacked us.

139
00:06:58,167 --> 00:07:00,086
- Right?
- Were you hurt?

140
00:07:02,046 --> 00:07:05,258
I'm okay. Good thing Sir Marcus showed up.

141
00:07:05,341 --> 00:07:07,635
And it turns out Jamilah
knows how to fight too.

142
00:07:07,718 --> 00:07:08,553
‪[tense sting]

143
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,723
Good thing you got there in time.

144
00:07:12,807 --> 00:07:14,183
You saved them.

145
00:07:17,979 --> 00:07:21,023
[music intensifies]

146
00:07:27,196 --> 00:07:30,533
It's always the same with you people.
You keep screwing up.

147
00:07:31,367 --> 00:07:32,243
Are you…

148
00:07:32,952 --> 00:07:34,871
[sniffles] …idiots?

149
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:36,622
- [man] Boss, please.
- [grunts, groans]

150
00:07:36,706 --> 00:07:38,207
- Boss!
- Bastard!

151
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:41,043
- [grunts, groans]
- Idiot!

152
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:42,253
- You too!
- [grunts]

153
00:07:42,336 --> 00:07:45,131
[groaning in pain]

154
00:07:45,214 --> 00:07:46,966
- Look at me.
- [sobbing]

155
00:07:47,049 --> 00:07:49,093
- Not the head, boss!
- What?

156
00:07:49,177 --> 00:07:51,971
- Do you want to live or die?
- [sobbing]

157
00:07:52,054 --> 00:07:55,141
- For now, I'll let you live.
- Boss!

158
00:07:55,224 --> 00:07:57,685
- [grunting]
- But I hope

159
00:07:57,768 --> 00:08:00,229
you've learned your lesson this time.

160
00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:03,232
[screaming]

161
00:08:03,316 --> 00:08:05,193
What?

162
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:08,321
For now, that's all you're getting!

163
00:08:08,404 --> 00:08:09,405
[grunts, groans]

164
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:13,117
- [unsettling music playing]
- [sighs]

165
00:08:13,201 --> 00:08:14,619
[shouts]

166
00:08:16,162 --> 00:08:17,997
[breathing heavily]

167
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:20,208
Damn you, Marcus.

168
00:08:21,751 --> 00:08:24,045
I should've had Jalil Abubakar by now,

169
00:08:24,921 --> 00:08:26,964
but you had to interfere again.

170
00:08:27,048 --> 00:08:29,675
[breathing heavily]

171
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:33,429
Next time, you're the one
I'm taking down, Marcus.

172
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:34,805
You bastard.

173
00:08:36,724 --> 00:08:38,768
- [laughing maniacally]
- [intense music playing]

174
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:42,188
I'll get my revenge on you.

175
00:08:42,271 --> 00:08:43,105
‪[music intensifies]

176
00:08:48,194 --> 00:08:49,195
[music concludes]

177
00:08:50,363 --> 00:08:53,616
A lot of frightening things
happened tonight, but…

178
00:08:54,492 --> 00:08:56,661
we still have so much to be grateful for.

179
00:08:57,537 --> 00:08:59,997
First of all, Marcus is back in service.

180
00:09:01,415 --> 00:09:06,212
Then, the successful mission
of Task Force Alpha.

181
00:09:07,713 --> 00:09:09,465
And most importantly,

182
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:14,178
Jamilah and Gracia made it back safely.

183
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:20,393
Alright, let's eat!

184
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:24,188
Jamilah… Do you want this?

185
00:09:24,272 --> 00:09:27,692
- [gentle music playing]
- [cutlery clinking]

186
00:09:30,653 --> 00:09:31,737
[in English] Sorry.

187
00:09:40,496 --> 00:09:41,539
You've got to try this.

188
00:09:42,039 --> 00:09:43,833
What else do you want?
This one is really good.

189
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:47,211
Juice? Do you want some juice?

190
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:48,713
Wow, Agent Flores!

191
00:09:48,796 --> 00:09:50,381
You're really taking
good care of her, huh!

192
00:09:50,464 --> 00:09:52,216
- I want that too!
- [laughing]

193
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:55,428
What if you also chew it for Gracia
so she won't get tired?

194
00:09:55,511 --> 00:09:57,388
Just eat over there, Sir Liam.

195
00:09:57,471 --> 00:09:58,848
Take care of me too.

196
00:09:58,931 --> 00:10:00,182
- [laughing]
- Here.

197
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:01,475
[Liam] No, I'm good.

198
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:02,560
- [cutlery clinking]
- [indistinct chatter]

199
00:10:02,643 --> 00:10:04,687
[Andre] Do you want some juice?

200
00:10:06,647 --> 00:10:09,025
[gentle music continues]

201
00:10:13,946 --> 00:10:17,116
[laid-back music playing]

202
00:10:21,746 --> 00:10:23,372
[in English] Dad rejected me.

203
00:10:24,832 --> 00:10:27,293
Even Marcus doesn't trust me anymore.

204
00:10:27,376 --> 00:10:28,377
[breath quivers]

205
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:30,588
[in English] I feel so isolated.

206
00:10:31,756 --> 00:10:33,299
[Raquel] I understand you, Lara.

207
00:10:33,382 --> 00:10:35,176
You're feeling isolated because…

208
00:10:36,052 --> 00:10:37,845
even Marcus doesn't trust you.

209
00:10:38,554 --> 00:10:39,889
But he's not important.

210
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:43,059
What's important is General.

211
00:10:45,436 --> 00:10:49,273
Lara, you know why I keep
telling you this, right?

212
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:52,193
[in English] I care about you.

213
00:10:53,444 --> 00:10:57,156
I was alone for a long time
before General rescued me.

214
00:10:57,823 --> 00:11:00,451
Then one day, he came home carrying you.

215
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,953
I was so happy then.

216
00:11:03,537 --> 00:11:06,332
I told myself I finally have
someone with me.

217
00:11:07,291 --> 00:11:10,878
I'll have a friend, a sister.

218
00:11:11,712 --> 00:11:13,631
That's why I don't want
to see you getting hurt

219
00:11:13,714 --> 00:11:15,383
or feeling sad like this.

220
00:11:18,302 --> 00:11:19,887
I don't know.

221
00:11:21,597 --> 00:11:24,141
I really don't know if I'm still
doing the right thing.

222
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:27,395
So many people
are getting dragged into this.

223
00:11:28,145 --> 00:11:29,313
Even the kids.

224
00:11:34,026 --> 00:11:37,029
I feel like I'm becoming
like the one who killed my parents.

225
00:11:39,156 --> 00:11:41,200
Lara, listen.

226
00:11:43,077 --> 00:11:46,038
Whatever General tells us to do,

227
00:11:46,122 --> 00:11:49,125
we follow it because that's what's right.

228
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:50,543
Okay?

229
00:11:51,419 --> 00:11:53,254
[phone ringing]

230
00:11:56,549 --> 00:11:57,633
‪[uneasy music playing]

231
00:11:59,093 --> 00:12:00,177
General.

232
00:12:01,679 --> 00:12:02,680
Yes, Gen.

233
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:04,557
I'm on my way.

234
00:12:10,896 --> 00:12:12,022
Miss.

235
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:14,400
You're looking really good.

236
00:12:15,484 --> 00:12:17,111
- [man grunts]
- [blow lands]

237
00:12:17,194 --> 00:12:18,195
- [thuds]
- [woman yelps]

238
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:20,156
That's what I like, a fighter.

239
00:12:20,906 --> 00:12:22,408
- [whack]
- [grunts]

240
00:12:22,491 --> 00:12:24,201
- [thuds]
- [grunts]

241
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:25,327
Go home!

242
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:27,204
[in English] And stop harassing women!

243
00:12:27,288 --> 00:12:29,540
Or else it'll be worse next time!

244
00:12:29,623 --> 00:12:30,583
[men grunting]

245
00:12:31,667 --> 00:12:34,420
[sinister music playing]

246
00:12:34,503 --> 00:12:36,464
[in English] Are you going
to be okay here alone?

247
00:12:37,673 --> 00:12:38,841
[inaudible] Yes.

248
00:12:50,019 --> 00:12:51,103
Sir Marcus.

249
00:12:51,687 --> 00:12:53,522
Why did you bring that?

250
00:12:53,606 --> 00:12:55,608
Uh, I just helped Doctor Teresa.

251
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:57,526
- [Marcus] Oh.
- I'll get going.

252
00:12:58,152 --> 00:12:59,445
Uh, Jamilah.

253
00:13:01,822 --> 00:13:02,990
Uh…

254
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:08,120
How's your… brother?

255
00:13:08,913 --> 00:13:11,749
Your brother, Jalil Abubakar?

256
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:16,462
[Jamilah] Oh, we don't talk.

257
00:13:16,545 --> 00:13:17,546
Why?

258
00:13:22,843 --> 00:13:25,221
I actually ran into him on the island.

259
00:13:26,138 --> 00:13:28,265
And it also happened
a few times here in Manila.

260
00:13:29,016 --> 00:13:32,478
We clashed several times
and almost killed each other.

261
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:41,862
So if you ever get the chance
to meet or talk to him,

262
00:13:42,446 --> 00:13:44,865
I want to apologize.

263
00:13:46,158 --> 00:13:47,743
Please tell him…

264
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:49,954
I understand him now.

265
00:13:52,248 --> 00:13:54,291
Everything is clear to me.

266
00:13:56,418 --> 00:13:59,588
I know why he did what he did.

267
00:14:01,131 --> 00:14:02,466
And to you too, Jamilah.

268
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:07,096
I want to say sorry…

269
00:14:08,931 --> 00:14:10,641
for everything that happened.

270
00:14:12,434 --> 00:14:13,519
Um…

271
00:14:14,436 --> 00:14:16,480
If I get to talk to Jalil,

272
00:14:17,314 --> 00:14:18,691
I'll make sure he hears everything.

273
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:21,652
[pensive music playing]

274
00:14:28,534 --> 00:14:30,202
[Usman] Auntie, we'll get going.

275
00:14:30,286 --> 00:14:32,121
- [Marcus] Did you all get full?
- Auntie, thank you so much.

276
00:14:32,204 --> 00:14:33,497
[Teresa] Thank you again.
I hope you enjoyed.

277
00:14:33,581 --> 00:14:36,000
- [Liam] Yes, very much.
- We really enjoyed it.

278
00:14:36,083 --> 00:14:36,959
Thank you again.

279
00:14:37,042 --> 00:14:38,502
See you next time.

280
00:14:38,586 --> 00:14:40,796
Gracia, I'll take you home.

281
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:44,008
Better like that in case
something happens to you again.

282
00:14:44,091 --> 00:14:45,384
Okay.

283
00:14:45,467 --> 00:14:48,053
After all, you already know
where I live anyway.

284
00:14:48,137 --> 00:14:51,307
- See? That's really so unfair!
- [slow clapping]

285
00:14:52,892 --> 00:14:55,603
Jamilah, I'll take you home.

286
00:14:57,062 --> 00:14:58,731
So you can get back safely.

287
00:14:58,814 --> 00:15:02,610
Those guys who tried to kidnap you
might still be out there.

288
00:15:02,693 --> 00:15:05,988
[Espina] Reyes, I'll take her.

289
00:15:06,071 --> 00:15:08,157
I know where she lives.

290
00:15:10,618 --> 00:15:12,328
Jamilah is my responsibility.

291
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:13,913
I was the one who brought her here.

292
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:18,918
Alright. Take care, both of you.

293
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:20,419
[Gracia] Take care, okay?

294
00:15:20,502 --> 00:15:22,379
Just text me when you get home.

295
00:15:23,172 --> 00:15:24,882
[Jamilah] Thank you again, Doctor Teresa.

296
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:27,092
- [Marcus] I'll just drop her off.
- Okay.

297
00:15:27,176 --> 00:15:28,344
- Take care.
- [Gracia] Thank you, Doc.

298
00:15:28,427 --> 00:15:29,845
- Thank you!
- [all] Thank you, Auntie!

299
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:31,639
- [Ryan] Bye, Auntie.
- Thank you! Hope you guys got full.

300
00:15:31,722 --> 00:15:33,057
- [Gracia] Thank you!
- [Liam] Hope there's a next time.

301
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:34,725
- Sure, anytime!
- Thank you again, Auntie.

302
00:15:34,808 --> 00:15:35,935
Take care!

303
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:39,104
Doctor, thank you very much.

304
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:40,356
I'll get going.

305
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:43,484
- Good night.
- Take care.

306
00:15:44,568 --> 00:15:45,527
Sabdani.

307
00:15:46,278 --> 00:15:49,323
[pensive music playing]

308
00:15:53,744 --> 00:15:56,163
- [Jamilah] Sir Marcus, I'll get off here.
- [seatbelt chimes]

309
00:16:08,968 --> 00:16:10,010
[groans]

310
00:16:22,106 --> 00:16:23,190
Uh…

311
00:16:23,273 --> 00:16:25,943
Sir Marcus, thank you for driving me home.

312
00:16:26,026 --> 00:16:28,779
And thank you again.

313
00:16:28,862 --> 00:16:31,782
This is the second time
you've helped save me.

314
00:16:33,158 --> 00:16:35,077
You saved me too, Jamilah.

315
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:36,704
- [thwacks]
- [man grunts]

316
00:16:36,787 --> 00:16:38,414
[grunts]

317
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:42,418
Oh, that makes sense.

318
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:45,629
You're pretty good in a fight.

319
00:16:46,213 --> 00:16:47,256
[chuckles softly, mouth clicks]

320
00:16:47,339 --> 00:16:51,051
That was actually the first time
I used it in a real fight.

321
00:16:51,135 --> 00:16:54,138
When it happened
at the hospital, I panicked.

322
00:16:54,221 --> 00:16:56,598
They had guns.

323
00:16:56,682 --> 00:17:00,352
But after that, I realized…

324
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:04,231
I can't let fear take over,

325
00:17:04,314 --> 00:17:07,693
because it'll only put me in more danger.

326
00:17:08,444 --> 00:17:09,653
That's true.

327
00:17:11,113 --> 00:17:14,366
But of course, you still have
to be careful all the time.

328
00:17:15,659 --> 00:17:17,327
When you're at a disadvantage,

329
00:17:17,411 --> 00:17:21,582
just make sure your objective
is to survive.

330
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:26,920
Look for the right timing
to turn the fight around,

331
00:17:27,004 --> 00:17:29,715
or more importantly, to escape.

332
00:17:31,258 --> 00:17:32,885
Are you teaching me now?

333
00:17:32,968 --> 00:17:34,344
[both chuckle]

334
00:17:35,679 --> 00:17:37,973
I just want you to be safe all the time.

335
00:17:39,475 --> 00:17:40,517
Thank you.

336
00:17:42,269 --> 00:17:43,771
Uh…

337
00:17:43,854 --> 00:17:45,731
Jamilah, I…

338
00:17:45,814 --> 00:17:49,318
I actually thought of something, if…
if it's okay with you.

339
00:17:49,401 --> 00:17:51,987
Of course, I want you safe.

340
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:54,656
If you're okay with it, maybe…

341
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:57,284
starting tomorrow…

342
00:17:57,367 --> 00:17:59,912
I can be the one to drive you
to and from the hospital.

343
00:18:01,121 --> 00:18:02,915
I wake up early anyway.

344
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:06,251
H-Huh? Wait.

345
00:18:06,335 --> 00:18:07,753
You don't have to, Sir Marcus.

346
00:18:07,836 --> 00:18:10,255
I don't want to impose.

347
00:18:10,339 --> 00:18:15,385
I can have Uncle Omar
take me to and from work.

348
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:18,680
- But--
- You saw me, didn't you?

349
00:18:18,764 --> 00:18:20,265
I know how to fight.

350
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:24,645
I can defend myself.

351
00:18:26,688 --> 00:18:28,232
- Alright.
- Okay.

352
00:18:28,315 --> 00:18:29,483
- Okay, then…
- [in English] Good night.

353
00:18:30,526 --> 00:18:31,652
[in English] Good night.

354
00:18:33,695 --> 00:18:34,738
Take care.

355
00:18:35,656 --> 00:18:38,158
[pensive music playing]

356
00:18:42,871 --> 00:18:45,124
[engine starts]

357
00:18:55,509 --> 00:18:58,470
[pensive music continues]

358
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:10,482
Jamilah, are you sure you're okay?

359
00:19:10,566 --> 00:19:12,234
[Jamilah] <i>Yes, Jalil.</i>

360
00:19:12,317 --> 00:19:16,572
I used the self-defense moves
you taught me.

361
00:19:17,281 --> 00:19:20,450
Auntie Norhana and Uncle Omar

362
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:22,536
are keeping a close eye on me.

363
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:25,289
Sitti won't let me
out of her sight either.

364
00:19:25,372 --> 00:19:26,915
[Jalil] <i>That's good.</i>

365
00:19:28,167 --> 00:19:30,085
But don't worry.

366
00:19:30,169 --> 00:19:33,755
I will find out who tried to abduct you.

367
00:19:34,715 --> 00:19:36,675
I won't let this happen again.

368
00:19:36,758 --> 00:19:38,510
I know, Jalil.

369
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:39,636
[in Tausug] Thank you.

370
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:40,929
Take care, brother.

371
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:42,347
You too.

372
00:19:43,390 --> 00:19:49,313
[morose music playing]

373
00:19:55,152 --> 00:19:55,986
Agent Angeles.

374
00:19:57,029 --> 00:19:58,030
Good morning.

375
00:20:03,118 --> 00:20:06,163
[tense music playing]

376
00:20:10,209 --> 00:20:11,627
That's what you were
wearing yesterday, Lara.

377
00:20:13,003 --> 00:20:14,087
Did you not go home?

378
00:20:14,171 --> 00:20:15,297
Leave me alone.

379
00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:23,180
[sighs]

380
00:20:24,723 --> 00:20:27,893
Do you all have to come with me to work?

381
00:20:27,976 --> 00:20:30,187
[chuckles] Of course!

382
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:33,690
To make sure no bad people get near you.

383
00:20:33,774 --> 00:20:37,236
[Omar] We're not taking any chances
after last night.

384
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:39,154
I promised Jalil I'd keep you safe.

385
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:42,324
Yeah. If anyone messes with you again,

386
00:20:42,407 --> 00:20:44,534
- we'll beat them up.
- Shh!

387
00:20:44,618 --> 00:20:48,330
Be extra careful, Jamilah.

388
00:20:48,413 --> 00:20:49,873
If there's any problem,
any problem at all,

389
00:20:49,957 --> 00:20:52,459
call us right away, okay?

390
00:20:53,293 --> 00:20:56,546
When it's time to go home,
call us, and we'll pick you up.

391
00:20:57,673 --> 00:20:59,591
[exhales, in Tausug] Thank you.

392
00:21:00,926 --> 00:21:02,636
- I'll go in now.
- Okay.

393
00:21:02,719 --> 00:21:03,971
- Take care.
- Bye.

394
00:21:04,054 --> 00:21:06,139
- Call if you need anything.
- [Jamilah] Mm-hmm.

395
00:21:06,223 --> 00:21:09,434
[suspenseful music playing]

396
00:21:25,033 --> 00:21:26,243
Are you ready?

397
00:21:27,202 --> 00:21:28,495
- [in English] Yes, sir.
- [in English] Yes, sir.

398
00:21:28,996 --> 00:21:31,206
[in English] Okay, let's begin.

399
00:21:34,334 --> 00:21:37,629
[morose music playing]

400
00:21:52,519 --> 00:21:55,063
‪[music turns tense]

401
00:22:03,447 --> 00:22:07,242
<i>How did you operate within the NLEA?</i>

402
00:22:07,909 --> 00:22:10,996
Who else was involved in this?

403
00:22:12,748 --> 00:22:14,124
Colonel Del Mundo.

404
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,626
He was the one who recruited us.

405
00:22:17,461 --> 00:22:20,839
He tasked us with manipulating
police assignments

406
00:22:20,922 --> 00:22:25,635
to protect the syndicate's transactions
from within.

407
00:22:27,054 --> 00:22:28,680
But he became greedy.

408
00:22:28,764 --> 00:22:30,766
He didn't divide the money fairly.

409
00:22:30,849 --> 00:22:31,725
[Azuelo] What?!

410
00:22:31,808 --> 00:22:37,606
You committed this betrayal
because of money?

411
00:22:37,689 --> 00:22:38,982
What did you think, sir?

412
00:22:39,066 --> 00:22:41,485
Money runs the world.

413
00:22:41,568 --> 00:22:44,446
[tense music continues]

414
00:22:45,572 --> 00:22:48,700
If you're really after the money,

415
00:22:48,784 --> 00:22:52,079
why are you selling
the smuggled weapons so cheaply?

416
00:22:52,162 --> 00:22:54,456
You were practically
giving them away for a bargain!

417
00:22:54,539 --> 00:22:55,999
What's your plan exactly?

418
00:22:56,083 --> 00:23:00,712
We'll make more if people can afford it.

419
00:23:01,630 --> 00:23:03,715
[Azuelo] Just tell the truth.

420
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:05,759
You want chaos!

421
00:23:05,842 --> 00:23:07,094
Then what?

422
00:23:07,886 --> 00:23:09,513
[in English] Destabilization?

423
00:23:09,596 --> 00:23:11,807
This is business, sir. All money.

424
00:23:12,891 --> 00:23:15,352
Selling the weapons at a bargain

425
00:23:15,435 --> 00:23:19,564
is a small sacrifice
for greater long-term profit.

426
00:23:19,648 --> 00:23:23,443
[Yulo] The proliferation of weapons
and rising crime

427
00:23:24,152 --> 00:23:27,864
are only the beginning of a larger scheme.

428
00:23:27,948 --> 00:23:30,659
When chaos grips the country,

429
00:23:30,742 --> 00:23:32,494
fear takes over.

430
00:23:32,577 --> 00:23:37,541
[Yulo] <i>Fear drives demand</i>
<i>for weapons and protection.</i>

431
00:23:37,624 --> 00:23:41,169
When demand rises, so do our prices.

432
00:23:41,253 --> 00:23:46,049
In the end, they will be forced
to arm themselves

433
00:23:46,133 --> 00:23:48,635
at any cost.

434
00:23:50,178 --> 00:23:51,388
[slams table]

435
00:23:52,764 --> 00:23:55,433
[tense music continues]

436
00:23:56,226 --> 00:23:58,270
[Valdez] But Colonel Del Mundo

437
00:23:58,353 --> 00:24:01,064
wanted it all for himself.

438
00:24:04,985 --> 00:24:05,986
[gun fires]

439
00:24:06,903 --> 00:24:09,948
[tense music continues]

440
00:24:12,993 --> 00:24:14,494
He became greedy,

441
00:24:14,578 --> 00:24:17,164
so we made his death look like a suicide.

442
00:24:21,293 --> 00:24:22,794
[Azuelo] Colonel Del Mundo

443
00:24:22,878 --> 00:24:27,632
was the one who gave the intel
about Datu Rahman Abubakar!

444
00:24:27,716 --> 00:24:29,092
[tense music swells]

445
00:24:29,176 --> 00:24:32,846
What's Datu Rahman's
involvement in all of this?!

446
00:24:32,929 --> 00:24:37,684
Datu Rahman was destroying
our main supply line

447
00:24:38,435 --> 00:24:39,895
near their island.

448
00:24:39,978 --> 00:24:42,105
[Valdez] <i>So we had to stop him.</i>

449
00:24:42,731 --> 00:24:44,232
<i>Too bad for him.</i>

450
00:24:44,316 --> 00:24:49,821
We made him the scapegoat.

451
00:24:50,488 --> 00:24:53,408
[Yulo] We made him
the face of the syndicate.

452
00:24:53,491 --> 00:24:56,369
And to make sure there were no loose ends,

453
00:24:56,453 --> 00:25:01,958
we eliminated the other members
of Task Force Alpha.

454
00:25:03,126 --> 00:25:08,423
[Yulo] <i>Lapeña, Marquez, and Contreras.</i>

455
00:25:08,506 --> 00:25:11,551
[tense music continues]

456
00:25:11,635 --> 00:25:14,512
We framed Datu Rahman's
so-called syndicate

457
00:25:14,596 --> 00:25:16,598
as the killers

458
00:25:16,681 --> 00:25:19,726
to piss off the entire police force.

459
00:25:19,809 --> 00:25:23,104
And while the NLEA was busy

460
00:25:23,188 --> 00:25:25,190
searching for Datu Rahman,

461
00:25:26,483 --> 00:25:30,237
we were able to operate freely.

462
00:25:32,405 --> 00:25:36,159
[music intensifies]

463
00:25:55,971 --> 00:25:58,014
[music concludes]

464
00:26:00,850 --> 00:26:04,896
They used Datu Rahman Abubakar
as a fall guy.

465
00:26:04,980 --> 00:26:08,066
[in English] Everything
is falling into place.

466
00:26:08,149 --> 00:26:10,277
- It feels overly orchestrated.
- What if it's a setup?

467
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:12,904
[Marcus] <i>I don't have any proof yet, but…</i>

468
00:26:12,988 --> 00:26:14,572
- General Carillo.
- General Carillo.

469
00:26:14,656 --> 00:26:16,032
I have my eye on him.

470
00:26:16,116 --> 00:26:18,702
[Marcus] <i>Lara must be involved somehow.</i>

471
00:26:18,785 --> 00:26:21,079
[in English] Dad told us
we’re this close to winning.

472
00:26:21,162 --> 00:26:22,497
[in English] Now is not
the time to go rogue.

473
00:26:22,580 --> 00:26:24,249
You should be telling yourself that.

474
00:26:24,332 --> 00:26:27,210
Datu Rahman has been proven innocent.

475
00:26:27,294 --> 00:26:31,089
[Jamilah] <i>We don't have to hide</i>
<i>anymore, Father.</i>

476
00:26:31,172 --> 00:26:32,924
[Azuelo] <i>He is still in danger.</i>

477
00:26:33,008 --> 00:26:36,553
<i>We must protect him</i>
<i>while he's under NLEA's custody.</i>

478
00:26:37,887 --> 00:26:41,099
[Ahmad] With how sophisticated
the syndicate’s actions are,

479
00:26:41,182 --> 00:26:47,147
only General Carillo could be behind this.

480
00:26:47,230 --> 00:26:51,026
And when they think it’s all over,

481
00:26:51,109 --> 00:26:52,736
we move in.

482
00:26:52,819 --> 00:26:55,989
They’re planning something
far bigger and deadlier.
